 most recently elected to that seat in 2005.

Galloway is perhaps best known for his vigorous campaign to both overturn economic sanctions against Iraq in the 1990s and early 2000s, and to avert the 2003 invasion of that country, as well as for his speech before the then President of Iraq, Saddam Hussein, in which he appeared to praise the Iraqi dictator,[2] although Galloway actively opposed the regime until the United States-led Gulf War in 1991 and has always stated that he was addressing the Iraqi people.&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
&lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/meccaone?a=ml8AbAaMtlY:1fEghSsRQY0:yIl2AUoC8zA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/meccaone?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/meccaone?a=ml8AbAaMtlY:1fEghSsRQY0:qj6IDK7rITs"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/meccaone?d=qj6IDK7rITs" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/meccaone?a=ml8AbAaMtlY:1fEghSsRQY0:V_sGLiPBpWU"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/meccaone?i=ml8AbAaMtlY:1fEghSsRQY0:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/meccaone?a=ml8AbAaMtlY:1fEghSsRQY0:gIN9vFwOqvQ"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/meccaone?i=ml8AbAaMtlY:1fEghSsRQY0:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
